      {
        "id": 11370,
        "name": "Markus Pilman",
        "username": "markus.pilman",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/{size}/379_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-07-01T14:10:20.929Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"nishanthapk\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"3414\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/nishanthapk/48/1365_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> nishanthapk:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>My question is, does client communicate only with IP addresses in cluster file ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, there\u2019s some work being done to also allow DNS names, but for now only IP addresses work.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"nishanthapk\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"3414\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/nishanthapk/48/1365_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> nishanthapk:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We are trying to expose foundationdb as a service to the public internet.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This seems risky to me. Instead you might want to consider putting some proxy in front. Currently, the only security-measure FDB provides is mTLS, but it is not meant to be a publicly available service. For example, we don\u2019t protect properly against DDoS attacks (and with mTLS these kind of attacks would be trivial to execute against FDB. Depending on what you are trying to do, mTLS would also not be a practical authentication mechanism.</p>",
        "post_number": 2,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2022-07-01T14:10:20.929Z",
        "reply_count": 2,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
        "quote_count": 1,
        "incoming_link_count": 1,
